4 contributions
Something Fishy Going On Here … And it's Worth a Visit!
Mar 2024 • Family
Nice big tank - not necessarily an "aquarium" with lots of tanks - though the tank there is quite large. Lots of interesting fish, some small sharks and rays. It sits right between the Casino and Bass Pro Shop, so if you're not into the casino scene, enter through Bass Pro Shop to access the aquarium. There's a seating area so you can relax while you watch the fish go by. It's not really a destination, but since it's free … plus the attraction is right across the freeway from where we were staying at Oasis RV resort, and since we needed a few things at Bass Pro Shop anyway, the location for us was perfect. Not sure I'd plan to make "a day" out of this place, however. It's maybe half-an-hour. There are feeding times at around 1PM and 4PM, but we weren't there for that. It might be more crowded at those times, but we had plenty of room to find a seat and watch the fish.
Written March 26, 2024

Pleasant aquarium… And free!
Nov 2023 • Family
You can pay $30 and see the aquarium at the Mandalay Bay. Or you can come here and see the fish for free. Not only that but after 4 PM several days a week, a mermaid swims with the fish. The aquarium tank is quite large and there are many different kinds of fish. Nothing too exciting but the small kids will probably find this enjoyable.
